  - m_Id: 6724759026008064
    m_Localized: Items You Collected
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6738791158120448
    m_Localized: Black pepper was one of the most valuable commodities in the Nusantara
      Spice Route trade. This spice was highly sought after by European nations because
      it was used as a food seasoning, natural preservative, and traditional medicine
      ingredient. Its high economic value made pepper-producing regions important
      centers of trade during the colonial era.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6738794341597184
    m_Localized: Clove is a spice native to the Maluku Islands with a strong aroma
      and high market value. During the spice trade era between the 16th and 18th
      centuries, cloves became one of the main reasons European nations came to the
      Nusantara to control trade routes and production sources.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6738796019318784
    m_Localized: Nutmeg is a famous spice originating from the Banda Islands in Maluku.
      During the colonial period, nutmeg had extremely high economic value, leading
      to intense competition among European powers to control its production areas.
      Besides being used as a cooking spice, nutmeg was also utilized for medicine
      and perfume.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6738798405877760
    m_Localized: Black Pepper
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6739371880480768
    m_Localized: Clove
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6739433008267264
    m_Localized: Nutmeg
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6740189031563264
    m_Localized: Cinnamon
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6740306576932864
    m_Localized: Cinnamon is known as a spice with a sweet aroma that is widely used
      in food, beverages, and traditional medicine. It became one of the important
      commodities in the Spice Route due to its high demand in European and Middle
      Eastern markets during the era of international trade.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6740491222777856
    m_Localized: Cardamom
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6740799218909184
    m_Localized: Cardamom is a spice commonly used in food, beverages, and traditional
      medicine in many parts of the world. In the history of the spice trade, cardamom
      became a valuable commodity because of its distinctive aroma and its health
      benefits that attracted foreign merchants.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6740907872354304
    m_Localized: The Dutch Guilder was the currency used by the Dutch colonial government
      and became an important medium of exchange in the spice trade across the Nusantara.
      It was used in commercial transactions involving local merchants, trading companies,
      and colonial authorities.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6741085337550848
    m_Localized: Dutch Guilder
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6741163720704000
    m_Localized: Trade Document
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6741308407414784
    m_Localized: Trade documents were official records used in spice trading activities,
      including sales agreements, ship cargo manifests, and trading permits. These
      documents played an important role in regulating spice distribution routes
      and maintaining trade relations between regions and nations during the historical
      spice trade era.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
